        <h1>The Second Earth Universe</h1>
        <ul class="normal-text">
            <li> The idea for Second Earth was born during a writing workshop at <b>SLOTART</b>. It was a turning point
                for me — I realized that what fascinates me most isn’t just creating fantastical worlds, but asking
                existential questions through them. I also discovered I didn’t want to answer those questions myself — I
                wanted to leave that to others. </li>
            <li> The premise was simple: to find out who we truly are as humanity. What happens when Earthlings meet...
                other Earthlings? Deep down, what do we really expect from ourselves? </li>
            <li> I added some reflections on the power of information — how deeply it affects us depending on its
                source, how complete it is, and how easily (or not) we can be manipulated. </li>
            <li> Then I spiced it all up with two multi-layered, complex protagonists. What kind of secrets might
                someone hide when the whole world is watching them? And could the toughest person be a man who despises
                weapons? </li>
            <li> Since then, Second Earth has evolved — gaining more nuance, themes, and mysteries. It keeps asking new
                questions and becoming more tightly interwoven with gameplay ideas. I invite you to explore the
                materials I’ve prepared — and maybe even answer for yourself: what do *I* expect from Second Earth?
            </li>
        </ul>
